text=(:if [ authgroup @tas || authgroup @admins || equal {$Author} '' ]:)%0a%0a(:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%0a>>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%0a[[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=edit|Edit this page]] \\%0aStatus: {GradebookArticles.{$Name}$:Status} %0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a----%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a[[!{$:Category}]]%0a%0a!West-African Accent Discrimination in Lewiston, Maine %0a%0a:Author: ahmed%0a%0a'''Summary:''' \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aA look at a study of discrimination towards West-African accents in Lewiston, ME%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aA study titled, “The ‘Forever Migrant: An Intersectional Analysis of L/A Workplace Discrimination on the Basis of Race, African Accent, and English Language Proficiency” was a linguistic study performed in the town of Lewiston, ME to study workplace discrimination towards specific racialized identities. The study interviewed multiple participants while also looking at relevant sociodemographic factors to identify and qualitatively describe discrimination of non-white individuals with African Accents in the workplace. The study found that those who learned English as a second language with an African accent were perceived and misclassified into harmful migrant and refugee stereotypes. This led to the creation of the term “forever migrant”, to describe the forced identity of those who spoke a variety of West-African accented English. One specific linguistic feature that many participants commented on was difficulties in distinguishing whether a sentence or phrase exhibited compositional or non-compositional meaning. An example of this occurred when a participant described how their manager and coworkers did not want to continue their training for their use of work computers, as the participant struggled to understand what their manager meant by the phrase "open the computer." This led to instances of frustration or discrimination with native-speakers, and in one instance bias in work performance evaluations. %0a%0a%0ahttps://scarab.bates.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1442&context=honorstheses%0ahttps://www.forbes.com/sites/janicegassam/2022/11/18/accent-discrimination-is-still-a-pervasive-issue-in-the-workplace-research-finds/?sh=523eb377697e%0ahttps://www.bbc.com/worklife/article/20210528-the-pervasive-problem-of-linguistic-racism%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Expansions:%0a[[#expansions]]%0a#foxbegin 221209-214515-988770#%0a(:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a!!!Trust & Accents %0a-> - pwchan%0a-> [-09.12.2022 - 13:45-]%0a>>rfloat%3c%3c   %0a(:if1 authgroup @tas:)%0a{[foxdelrange button 221209-214515-988770 {$FullName} ]}%0a(:if1end:)%0a>>%3c%3c%0a(:div1end:) %0a>>messageitem%3c%3c %0ahttps://www.scientificamerican.com/article/the-brain-doubts-accent/%0a%0aThe above article provides a bit of insight as to why workplace discrimination toward those with accents occurs. Mainly, employers may see accents as an impairment of cooperation and work. While it is true that accents, for a native speaker of the "standard" form of the language, are more difficult to understand, this should not change how trustworthy the information itself actually is. However, a study noted in this article found that a foreign or different accent would make the exact same message or statement seem less trustworthy to the participants. This drop in trust could be instrumental to the issue of workplace discrimination as a result of how one speaks. %0a>>%3c%3c%0a#foxend 221209-214515-988770#%0a[[#expansionsend]]%0a%0a----%0a%25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%0a(:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%0a(:elseif [ equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:andrewid} '' || equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:section} '' ] :)%0a%0aYou must enter your andrew ID and section before submitting an expansion. %0a%0a(:else:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Comments%0a%0a%0a%0a%0a----%0a(:if equal {$Author} {$:Author}:)%0a!!Change article category%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#changearticlecategory:)%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a%0a(:Section: E:)%0a(:Category: LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild:)%0a(:Title: West-African Accent Discrimination in Lewiston, Maine :)
